     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="6"/>
   <head>To the Author vpon his
Poem.</head>
   <l>VVHile other Muses wanton Poems sing,</l>
   <l>Thy pen being taken from a Cherubs wing</l>
   <l>Teacheth the way to blisse, where they and we</l>
   <l>Meet in a quire, to adore Eternitie</l>
   <l>Death must begin our triumph, and the dust</l>
   <l>That hangs vpon our fleshie garment must</l>
   <l>Be first brush'd of, the vanities of life</l>
   <l>Riches and pleasures, that but sweeten strife</l>
   <l>And to the eye of sense makes death appeare</l>
   <l>Deform'd, by thy diuiner raptures here</l>
   <l>Are quite destroide, the rugged path made eauen</l>
   <l>And men acknowledge thee the way to Heauen.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Iames Sherlie.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
